Utah Teapot (teapot.g)

Originally modeled by Martin Newell at the University of Utah in 1975.

Despite the .g extension (normally BRL-CAD format), this file is an
ASCII triangle mesh — the same coordinate data as TeapotPoints.txt in
VTK's legacy format. It is not a BRL-CAD database.

No formal license has ever been issued for the original Newell dataset.
The model has been freely distributed in essentially every computer
graphics package since the mid-1970s (POV-Ray, Blender, 3ds Max, OpenGL
GLUT, VTK, etc.) and is conventionally treated as public domain. These
specific files have been redistributed as VTK test data since 2001
under VTK's BSD-3 license.

Recommended attribution: "Utah Teapot, originally modeled by Martin
Newell, University of Utah, 1975."

Background: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Utah_teapot

